      "id": "3d469c8816dc8766f52d1c9ec3f6fc2090c4f5bd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-18 21:15:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nPatch looks fine, apparently identical to the last one on bug 23547.\n\nMy only concern is about bug 23771 \"set the 'checksum' bit, but didn't send a checksum\".  How much have you tested this patch?\n\nIt would be good to know if the crc32c algorithm allows \"~0\" as a valid checksum value.  I wonder if that check is even correct, or if it should be removed?  It seems possible that \"~0\" is a valid checksum value in some algorithms, though I believe that \"0\" should never be valid.\n\nI suppose the other possibility is if the server didn't compute any checksum on 0 bytes of data for some reason, but in that case \"rc > 0\" should be false.\n\nSince 1.8.6 is frozen already, this couldn't be landed for\nthat release.  Please also submit a patch for 2.1 so that this feature can be used in the newer release as well (it is much more likely to land there quickly than on 1.8.x).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4b3a15d4867178fe84ec39664922ef1457c45477",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 164,
        "name": "Shuichi Ihara",
        "email": "sihara@ddn.com",
        "username": "ihara"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-19 04:40:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nnote, I did two fixes here against the last patch in 23549. \";\" was missing in __asm__ __volatile__() and return value \"crc\" was wrong in __u32 crc32c_hw().\n\nwe saw bug 23771 on SFA10KE which is our embedded system which is based on KVM. The problem was not always happened, so I'm looking for how reproduce bug 23771...\nI wonder if above two fixes could cause the problem?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
